    "narrative": "The Austin Waves are primed for a high-ceiling outing today, led by **Kyle Tucker** (85.90) and **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88). **Kyle Tucker** is our premier play; despite a neutral platoon split against Quintana, he benefits from a massive park factor boost and strong underlying xwOBA, anchoring our offense from the two-hole. **Gunnar Henderson** follows closely, buoyed by a favorable wind forecast and a classic leadoff spot against Lugo, whose 4.53 xERA offers plenty of upside. **Andy Pages** also projects as a high-tier start (74.43) as he looks to exploit the same Quintana matchup, leveraging a 14% park adjustment to maximize his power output.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the lineup today involved **Nolan Schanuel**, who sits on the bench with a 46.58 score. While he remains a capable asset, his matchup against a high-caliber arm in Cease (3.58 xERA) suppressed his potential compared to the high-leverage spots occupied by **Drake Baldwin** (71.27) and **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66), both of whom benefit from a soft matchup against Elder. We are also closely monitoring the lineup status of **Jacob Wilson** and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**; **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**, in particular, remains in our UTIL spot despite a tough assignment against Detmers (3.06 xERA), as his elite pedigree keeps his floor high enough to warrant the start over available alternatives.\n\nRisk management remains a priority given the volatility of our \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Jacob Wilson**, **Andy Pages**, **Josh Lowe**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.**. Any late-breaking changes to the batting order, especially regarding **Nasim Nunez**\u2014who is currently suppressed by a #9 spot\u2014could shift our strategy. We continue to navigate the absence of **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Jordan Westburg**, whose contributions are sorely missed as we lean on the depth of **Dominic Smith** and **Liam Hicks** to maintain efficiency. We will continue to prioritize stolen base threats like **Gunnar Henderson** and **Josh Lowe** to keep pace in our scarcest category.",
